# robot_config.yaml — Tutorial

This file is the main Nav2 parameter file for the robot. It configures every
node in the navigation stack: localization, costmaps, planner, controller,
behaviors, smoother, recovery, docking, sensor filtering, and the collision /
safety layer.

Path: [robot_config.yaml](robot_config.yaml)

> **Placeholders.** The file contains tokens that are substituted at launch
> time:
> - `<robot_namespace>` → robot namespace, e.g. `sirbot1`
> - `<frame_namespace>` → TF frame prefix, e.g. `sirbot1`
> - `<footprint>` → robot footprint polygon string
>
> Do **not** keep these literal `<...>` strings in a deployed file — the launch
> system rewrites them. If you copy this file by hand, replace them yourself.

---

